1
00:01:53,208 --> 00:01:54,875
[KYRIE] There are two
kinds of companions...

2
00:01:54,958 --> 00:01:56,583
Companions who are
bound to one another

3
00:01:56,666 --> 00:01:58,375
through the
bonds of friendship...

4
00:01:58,458 --> 00:02:00,750
and companions who waste
all of their time and energy

5
00:02:00,833 --> 00:02:02,500
arguing when
it's really hot out

6
00:02:02,583 --> 00:02:03,875
and they're sitting right
outside of an inn...

7
00:02:03,958 --> 00:02:04,750
[MORTE] Will you
just give it a rest

8
00:02:04,833 --> 00:02:06,208
and pipe down already, Toppy?!

9
00:02:06,291 --> 00:02:08,666
How many times do I have
to repeat myself to you?

10
00:02:09,333 --> 00:02:11,166
It's a human town;
there's no other option.

11
00:02:11,250 --> 00:02:13,666
[TOPPY] I won't pretend to
be a stuffed animal, kuma!

12
00:02:13,750 --> 00:02:15,125
Do you think I wanna
pretend to be walking around

13
00:02:15,208 --> 00:02:16,500
with a stuffed
animal at my age?

14
00:02:16,583 --> 00:02:18,250
No! But it's
what we have to do!

15
00:02:18,333 --> 00:02:20,041
[TOPPY] It's against
everything I stand for.

16
00:02:20,125 --> 00:02:22,083
I simply won't do it, kuma!

17
00:02:22,166 --> 00:02:24,000
Fine, then we'll just
pretend Kyrie and I

18
00:02:24,083 --> 00:02:25,708
are a couple and
you're our baby.

19
00:02:25,791 --> 00:02:26,958
Kuma!

20
00:02:27,041 --> 00:02:28,333
[MORTE] Perfect!
You're already crying and

21
00:02:28,416 --> 00:02:30,208
carrying on like a wittle baby!

22
00:02:30,291 --> 00:02:32,291
Can't we go inside? It's hot!

23
00:02:32,375 --> 00:02:34,458
[TOPPY and MORTE arguing]

24
00:02:34,541 --> 00:02:36,333
[INNKEEPER] Are you
three looking for a room?

25
00:02:36,416 --> 00:02:37,833
[All] Hm?

26
00:02:40,416 --> 00:02:42,625
[KYRIE] Well yes, we'd
love one if it's available,

27
00:02:42,708 --> 00:02:43,958
but you see...

28
00:02:44,041 --> 00:02:46,000
[chuckles] Your
friend is welcome.

29
00:02:46,083 --> 00:02:47,583
I would go out of
business if I started

30
00:02:47,666 --> 00:02:50,041
being choosy about my clientele.

31
00:02:50,125 --> 00:02:52,375
[KYRIE] Are you serious?!
Thank you so much!

32
00:02:52,458 --> 00:02:53,541
[TOPPY] Kuma!

33
00:02:53,625 --> 00:02:55,000
I do hate to ask this but...

34
00:02:55,083 --> 00:02:57,083
it's our policy to
collect payment first.

35
00:02:57,166 --> 00:02:58,333
Sure!

36
00:02:58,416 --> 00:02:59,791
[INNKEEPER] Splendid!
I'm glad that you three

37
00:02:59,875 --> 00:03:02,000
turned out to be decent
travelers after all.

38
00:03:02,083 --> 00:03:03,750
[KYRIE] What exactly
do you mean by that?

39
00:03:03,833 --> 00:03:05,291
Well I don't want
to scare you off,

40
00:03:05,375 --> 00:03:07,166
but I should warn you
that the World Destruction

41
00:03:07,250 --> 00:03:09,333
Committee has been
terrorizing this area.

42
00:03:09,416 --> 00:03:10,333
[KYRIE] Wha--?!

43
00:03:10,416 --> 00:03:11,250
[BOTH] Uh.

44
00:03:11,333 --> 00:03:12,625
Are you sure?

45
00:03:12,708 --> 00:03:14,541
Yeah the word is that
they've been robbing people

46
00:03:14,625 --> 00:03:17,333
and eating without paying. I
guess they're hard up for cash.

47
00:03:17,416 --> 00:03:19,833
[KYRIE] That's... unbelievable?

48
00:03:20,833 --> 00:03:21,958
Hm...

49
00:03:35,416 --> 00:03:37,208
[WAITRESS] I hope you
folks are enjoying your meal

50
00:03:37,291 --> 00:03:39,875
and I hate to ask again
but about the bill...

51
00:03:42,666 --> 00:03:44,958
[MAN] Tell me, have you
ever asked yourself...

52
00:03:45,041 --> 00:03:46,916
Why did the gods go
out of their way to place

53
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:50,250
the beastmen as well as
the humans within this world?

54
00:03:50,333 --> 00:03:51,750
Huh?

55
00:03:51,833 --> 00:03:53,458
[MAN] Some say they
were bitter after being

56
00:03:53,541 --> 00:03:55,208
dumped by the goddesses.

57
00:03:55,291 --> 00:03:57,875
Others say the gods accidentally
made two unique tribes

58
00:03:57,958 --> 00:04:00,375
because they were
distracted by demons.

59
00:04:01,250 --> 00:04:03,500
But this was no
accident, rather a message.

60
00:04:03,583 --> 00:04:05,583
"Hark! Let all
beings live together

61
00:04:05,666 --> 00:04:07,958
and let love
transcend the tribes!"

62
00:04:09,041 --> 00:04:11,083
Love...! That is
what the gods have

63
00:04:11,166 --> 00:04:12,458
truly intended for us!

64
00:04:12,541 --> 00:04:15,375
To unite all tribes
through the power of love!

65
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:19,208
[MAN] All the tribes,
not just man and beastman...

66
00:04:19,291 --> 00:04:22,291
but also the between
man and woman...

67
00:04:22,375 --> 00:04:24,375
Speaking of which...

68
00:04:24,458 --> 00:04:26,250
Seeing as how
you and I represent

69
00:04:26,333 --> 00:04:28,333
the tribes of male and female...

70
00:04:28,416 --> 00:04:31,083
I would love for us
to transcend together!

71
00:04:31,166 --> 00:04:32,750
Uh... Huh?!

72
00:04:32,833 --> 00:04:34,750
[MAN] Mmm. It's the
gods' will for us to

73
00:04:34,833 --> 00:04:37,000
unleash the power of love!

74
00:04:39,583 --> 00:04:41,291
[ALL gasp]

75
00:04:41,375 --> 00:04:43,000
Ow! What'd you
do that for?

76
00:04:43,083 --> 00:04:44,166
Couldn't you have
found a better way

77
00:04:44,250 --> 00:04:45,958
to tell me that you
were getting jealous?

78
00:04:46,041 --> 00:04:47,750
[WOMAN] You're making
an ass of yourself.

79
00:04:47,833 --> 00:04:49,083
Let's get outta here.

80
00:04:49,166 --> 00:04:51,375
[BEAR] Uh... Can you
guys please not fight here?

81
00:04:52,791 --> 00:04:55,166
Hold on... What about your bill?

82
00:04:55,250 --> 00:04:58,000
[MAN] This may
surprise you but I'm...

83
00:04:58,083 --> 00:04:59,875
I'm none other
than the feared Kyrie

84
00:04:59,958 --> 00:05:01,916
of the World
Destruction Committee!

85
00:05:03,791 --> 00:05:05,500
And I'm Morte.

86
00:05:05,583 --> 00:05:08,833
And that... makes me, Toppy.

87
00:05:08,916 --> 00:05:11,125
[screaming]

88
00:05:11,208 --> 00:05:13,208
Ha ha! I love to
hear the screaming!

89
00:05:13,291 --> 00:05:15,000
Now... if any of you
so much as think about

90
00:05:15,083 --> 00:05:17,166
going to the authorities,
we'll come back and give you

91
00:05:17,250 --> 00:05:19,000
all something to
really scream about...

92
00:05:19,083 --> 00:05:21,291
I hope I've made myself clear.

93
00:05:21,375 --> 00:05:22,750
[MAN] Ciao!

94
00:05:25,291 --> 00:05:27,208
[GIRL] Ahhh!

95
00:05:27,291 --> 00:05:28,750
Uh... Huh?

96
00:05:28,833 --> 00:05:30,750
I-I didn't mean to...

97
00:05:36,666 --> 00:05:38,666
[screaming]

98
00:05:40,791 --> 00:05:43,333
I'm sorry. Are you
okay little girl?

99
00:05:43,416 --> 00:05:44,208
[GIRL] Yep.

100
00:05:44,291 --> 00:05:45,458
It's time to leave.

101
00:05:45,541 --> 00:05:46,625
Right.

102
00:05:47,750 --> 00:05:49,416
[MAN] How much
longer will it be...

103
00:05:49,500 --> 00:05:52,041
before we reach the new world?

104
00:05:52,125 --> 00:05:54,250
[GIRL chuckles]

105
00:06:01,708 --> 00:06:04,083
[heavy exhales]

106
00:06:04,166 --> 00:06:05,541
[TOPPY] Kuma!

107
00:06:07,541 --> 00:06:09,416
After you rest up, we're
starting interrogations

108
00:06:09,500 --> 00:06:10,875
immediately, kuma!

109
00:06:10,958 --> 00:06:12,625
Are you still
going on about that?

110
00:06:12,708 --> 00:06:14,208
If these imposters
want the attention

111
00:06:14,291 --> 00:06:15,750
and can get the World
Salvation Committee

112
00:06:15,833 --> 00:06:17,541
off our backs,
it's a win-win.

113
00:06:17,625 --> 00:06:19,250
How can you say that, kuma?

114
00:06:19,333 --> 00:06:21,500
I, for one, cannot stand
here and let some petty thief

115
00:06:21,583 --> 00:06:23,291
drag my name
through the mud, kuma!

116
00:06:23,375 --> 00:06:26,291
If that's what you're concerned
about, you're a little late.

117
00:06:27,416 --> 00:06:28,791
Toppy, it would be
really nice if you just

118
00:06:28,875 --> 00:06:30,500
stayed here with
us and relaxed.

119
00:06:30,583 --> 00:06:32,041
[KYRIE] Especially after
they were nice enough to

120
00:06:32,125 --> 00:06:33,791
bring that special
bed in for you.

121
00:06:33,875 --> 00:06:35,375
Besides, you'd stick
out like a sore thumb

122
00:06:35,458 --> 00:06:37,291
if you went
investigating in town.

123
00:06:37,375 --> 00:06:39,375
So you'll take the fall for
a friend and be associated

124
00:06:39,458 --> 00:06:42,500
with stealing gambling money
but not the ol' dine and dash?

125
00:06:42,583 --> 00:06:43,958
Fine then, kuma!

126
00:06:44,041 --> 00:06:46,041
I just investigate
by myself, kuma!

127
00:06:46,125 --> 00:06:47,416
Toppy!

128
00:06:47,500 --> 00:06:50,000
[KYRIE] Just stop and
think about for a second...

129
00:06:50,083 --> 00:06:52,041
[BOTH stutter] Ahhh!

130
00:06:52,750 --> 00:06:54,125
[door shuts]

131
00:06:55,250 --> 00:06:57,291
Get off!

132
00:06:58,083 --> 00:06:59,500
Sorry, Morte.

133
00:07:07,625 --> 00:07:09,000
What's wrong?

134
00:07:09,083 --> 00:07:11,666
Uh...

135
00:07:11,750 --> 00:07:13,083
Nothing...

136
00:07:13,166 --> 00:07:14,833
[KYRIE] Oh man. How do you
tell a woman that already

137
00:07:14,916 --> 00:07:17,750
wants to kill you that
you tore her clothes?

138
00:07:19,750 --> 00:07:21,375
[RESTAURANT OWNER] I'm not
telling you people anything

139
00:07:21,458 --> 00:07:23,291
until you buy enough
food to compensate me

140
00:07:23,375 --> 00:07:25,666
for what they ate and
the damage they caused.

141
00:07:25,750 --> 00:07:28,000
Besides if the World
Salvation Committee

142
00:07:28,083 --> 00:07:30,250
had done their jobs, none of
this would've ever happened.

143
00:07:30,333 --> 00:07:31,625
Watch your tongue, human!

144
00:07:31,708 --> 00:07:33,250
The World Salvation
Committee is saving you

145
00:07:33,333 --> 00:07:35,541
from extinction and you
dare to think we owe you?

146
00:07:35,625 --> 00:07:36,875
No, I just meant that...

147
00:07:36,958 --> 00:07:39,708
How often must I tell you
not to use intimidation?

148
00:07:39,791 --> 00:07:41,750
Pardon me Nadja, but
I've had it with your rules.

149
00:07:41,833 --> 00:07:43,750
It's not as if any of your
calculations have brought

150
00:07:43,833 --> 00:07:46,125
the World Destruction
Committee into custody.

151
00:07:46,208 --> 00:07:48,541
Sorry you feel that
way but I disagree.

152
00:07:48,625 --> 00:07:50,125
My calculations
have been perfect

153
00:07:50,208 --> 00:07:52,458
yet lady luck hasn't
been on our side.

154
00:07:52,541 --> 00:07:55,166
[NADJA] But our time to strike
seems to be soon upon us.

155
00:07:55,250 --> 00:07:57,958
And looks like we're
having a meal until then.

156
00:07:58,041 --> 00:07:59,916
[LIA grunts]

157
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:02,916
One of everything they ate
for our special patrons.

158
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:04,250
[NADJA] Now your part.

159
00:08:04,333 --> 00:08:05,875
I heard they'd stolen a
number of priceless items

160
00:08:05,958 --> 00:08:07,875
from an antique
store in the next town.

161
00:08:07,958 --> 00:08:09,125
[NADJA] In the next town?

162
00:08:09,208 --> 00:08:12,583
That's right. The one
at the top of that hill.

163
00:08:12,666 --> 00:08:14,208
[RESTAURANT OWNER] It's
a beastman town so I rarely

164
00:08:14,291 --> 00:08:16,375
make it up there. If you
look close enough, though,

165
00:08:16,458 --> 00:08:18,250
you can probably see it.

166
00:08:19,541 --> 00:08:21,750
We have to walk
all the way up there?

167
00:08:21,833 --> 00:08:23,625
I hope you're hungry.

168
00:08:31,083 --> 00:08:32,291
[OLD COP] Ahhh!

169
00:08:32,375 --> 00:08:34,958
Beastmen sure do
come in all shapes and sizes.

170
00:08:35,041 --> 00:08:36,916
I've been the sheriff
of this town for many years

171
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:39,750
and you certainly are the
tiniest fellow I've ever seen.

172
00:08:39,833 --> 00:08:41,625
I'll take that as a
compliment and thank you

173
00:08:41,708 --> 00:08:43,625
for your years of
devoted service.

174
00:08:43,708 --> 00:08:45,666
Now can you describe
the criminal activities

175
00:08:45,750 --> 00:08:47,750
of the World Destruction
Committee, kuma?

176
00:08:47,833 --> 00:08:50,125
Well... there's not
much except some robberies

177
00:08:50,208 --> 00:08:52,625
and eating without paying.
Save for an incident

178
00:08:52,708 --> 00:08:55,625
in the next town where someone
was injured in a robbery.

179
00:08:55,708 --> 00:08:57,791
[TOPPY] These fiends
disgust me, kuma.

180
00:08:57,875 --> 00:09:00,041
[OLD COP] Looks to me like every
restaurant and antique shop

181
00:09:00,125 --> 00:09:02,666
in the area's been knocked
over by these criminals...

182
00:09:02,750 --> 00:09:04,458
Just today they
walked out on their bill

183
00:09:04,541 --> 00:09:06,916
and terrorized patrons
at a restaurant near here.

184
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:08,416
[TOPPY] How long ago?

185
00:09:08,500 --> 00:09:10,583
[OLD COP] Hm...
A few hours back,

186
00:09:10,666 --> 00:09:12,416
so I'm calling witnesses...

187
00:09:12,500 --> 00:09:16,166
[GIRL] Oh wow! This time
it's a teeny tiny bear! Yay!

188
00:09:16,250 --> 00:09:18,666
[TOPPY] Put me down, kuma!

189
00:09:19,416 --> 00:09:22,000
Don't call me
a bear, kuma.

190
00:09:22,083 --> 00:09:23,833
[GIRL] Mr. Policeman,
I don't get it.

191
00:09:23,916 --> 00:09:25,875
Why doesn't he wanna
be called a bear?

192
00:09:25,958 --> 00:09:27,708
[OLD COP] Maya put
the little bear down.

193
00:09:27,791 --> 00:09:30,541
Can't you see he doesn't
like to be handled like that?

194
00:09:31,291 --> 00:09:32,750
Maya, I need
your help.

195
00:09:32,833 --> 00:09:34,625
Can you be my star
witness and tell me

196
00:09:34,708 --> 00:09:36,375
what happened at
the restaurant?

197
00:09:36,458 --> 00:09:37,583
Mm! Yes, sir!

198
00:09:37,666 --> 00:09:39,125
The bear was way
bigger than this one

199
00:09:39,208 --> 00:09:40,291
and his name was
Toppy and he was

200
00:09:40,375 --> 00:09:42,791
really nice and
said he was sorry.

201
00:09:42,875 --> 00:09:44,666
He...
said he was sorry?

202
00:09:44,750 --> 00:09:47,250
He just looked really scary
'cause he was super huge

203
00:09:47,333 --> 00:09:50,416
but he was actually nice
and apologized just to me!

204
00:09:51,541 --> 00:09:53,708
I'm not a bear, kuma.

205
00:09:59,833 --> 00:10:02,208
[MORTE] Kyrie, look how
intricate this painting is...

206
00:10:02,291 --> 00:10:03,666
I think it's an original.

207
00:10:03,750 --> 00:10:05,666
[KYRIE] Oh wow... So deep...

208
00:10:05,750 --> 00:10:08,708
Just keep looking at how
pretty and intricate it is.

209
00:10:10,583 --> 00:10:13,166
[KYRIE nervous screaming]

210
00:10:13,250 --> 00:10:15,125
You okay?

211
00:10:15,208 --> 00:10:17,291
Needed some fresh air.

212
00:10:18,541 --> 00:10:19,916
[KYRIE] Is that a...

213
00:10:21,791 --> 00:10:23,791
[KYRIE] Hey Morte!
You gotta see this.

214
00:10:23,875 --> 00:10:25,916
Come on...
Look at that building.

215
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:27,541
Maybe we could go together.

216
00:10:27,625 --> 00:10:29,333
[MORTE] Huh? Go where?

217
00:10:31,916 --> 00:10:33,541
The one across the
way with the chimney.

218
00:10:33,625 --> 00:10:36,041
It looks like it's
the town bathhouse.

219
00:10:38,250 --> 00:10:40,125
[trembling] Uh...

220
00:10:40,208 --> 00:10:43,916
So how's about you and
I go and relax together, Morte!

221
00:10:44,833 --> 00:10:46,250
Bathe together?

222
